## Reset Verification Procedures

### Post-Reset Health Checks
```bash
#!/bin/bash
echo "🔍 Running post-reset health checks..."

# Check service availability
curl -f http://localhost:3000/health || echo "❌ Agency Hub health check failed"
curl -f http://localhost:3001/health || echo "❌ MCP Server health check failed"
nc -z localhost 3002 && echo "✅ WebSocket server is responsive" || echo "❌ WebSocket check failed"

# Check database connectivity
npm run db:test || echo "❌ Database connectivity failed"

# Check agent registration
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/agents/register \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"agentId":"health-check","name":"Health Check Agent","role":"test"}' \
  || echo "❌ Agent registration failed"

# Check WebSocket connection
node -e "
const WebSocket = require('ws');
const ws = new WebSocket('ws://localhost:3002');
ws.on('open', () => {
  console.log('✅ WebSocket connection successful');
  ws.close();
});
ws.on('error', () => {
  console.log('❌ WebSocket connection failed');
});
" || echo "❌ WebSocket test failed"

echo "🔍 Health checks complete!"
```

### Reset Rollback Procedures
```bash
#!/bin/bash
# Rollback procedures if reset fails

echo "🔙 Starting rollback procedures..."

# Stop current services
./stop-development.sh

# Restore from backup
if [ -d "backups/$(date +%Y%m%d)" ]; then
    echo "📦 Restoring from today's backup..."
    
    # Restore database
    psql agency_hub < backups/$(date +%Y%m%d)/agency_hub_backup.sql
    
    # Restore configuration
    cp backups/$(date +%Y%m%d)/.env .env
    
    # Restore logs
    cp -r backups/$(date +%Y%m%d)/logs/* logs/
    
    echo "✅ Rollback complete!"
else
    echo "❌ No backup found for today!"
    echo "🔧 Performing emergency reset to last known good state..."
    
    # Emergency reset to defaults
    cp .env.example .env
    npm run db:seed:default
fi

# Restart services
./start-development.sh
```

## Automated Reset Scripts

### Scheduled Maintenance Reset
```bash
#!/bin/bash
# Cron job for regular maintenance resets
# 0 2 * * 0 /path/to/maintenance-reset.sh

echo "🕐 Starting scheduled maintenance reset..."

# Create backup
./backup-system.sh

# Clear logs older than 7 days
find logs/ -name "*.log" -mtime +7 -delete

# Clear temporary files
rm -rf tmp/* .cache/* node_modules/.cache/*

# Update dependencies (patch level only)
npm update

# Restart services
./restart-all-services.sh

echo "✅ Scheduled maintenance complete!"
```

### Emergency Reset Script
```bash
#!/bin/bash
# Emergency reset for critical failures

echo "🚨 EMERGENCY RESET INITIATED"

# Immediate service shutdown
pkill -9 -f "agency|mcp|websocket"

# Quick backup
mkdir -p emergency-backup/$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M%S)
cp .env emergency-backup/$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M%S)/
pg_dump agency_hub > emergency-backup/$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M%S)/db_backup.sql

# Fast reset to working state
cp .env.emergency .env
npm run db:reset:emergency
npm run start:minimal

echo "🆘 Emergency reset complete - minimal services running"
```

